## DECENTRALIZED MEMORY ARCHITECTURE

**V2 Enhancement**: Metadata + usage tracking + nexus-graph pattern linking

```
φ-tier: GREMLIN-BRAIN-V2 (this) → Dewey index, always in context
  ↓
π-tier: MONAD-MEMORY → Regeneration/connection layer
  ↓
e-tier: NEXUS-CORE → Base concepts, active working memory
  ↓
i-tier: NEXUS-MIND → Deep memory, large files, mastery
  ↓
NEXUS-GRAPH → Pattern/meta-pattern links (φ.X.X.X → π.Y.Y.Y → e.Z.Z.Z)

Each tier complements the others.
Load in combinations based on task complexity.
Metadata always available at φ-tier.
Nexus-graph maps which Dewey IDs link to which.
```

---

## DECIMAL STRUCTURE

```
[MORPHEME].[CATEGORY].[DOMAIN].[FILE#]

Morpheme Prefix (cognitive tier):
  φ = seed-tier       (~100 tokens, indices/references)
  π = structure-tier  (100-500 tokens, frameworks)
  e = current-tier    (500-2000 tokens, active work)
  i = deep-tier       (2000+ tokens, mastery/unconscious)

Category (0-9):
  0 = System/Index
  1 = Entities (WHO)
  2 = Theory (WHAT)
  3 = Methodology (HOW)
  4 = History (WHEN)
  5 = Connections (TOPOLOGY) ← nexus-graph lives here
  6 = Research
  7 = Applications
  8 = Memory Architecture
  9 = References

Domain (0-9): Subcategory
File# (1-999): Sequential
```

**V2 Navigation**:
```bash
find_tier φ/π/e/i  # Filter by cognitive tier
find_cat 0-9       # Jump to category
find_links X.Y.Z   # Show what this Dewey ID links to (nexus-graph)
find_hot           # Most-used files (V2)
find_pattern P     # Find pattern in nexus-graph
```

