## AUTONOMOUS MAINTENANCE PROTOCOLS

**How Claude maintains this system autonomously:**

### φ-tier: GREMLIN-BRAIN-V2 (this file)
```bash
# When: After any session involving file access
# What: Update access logs
echo "$(date -Iseconds)|φ.X.X.X|context_description" >> .claude/brain/access_log

# When: New skill created
# What: Add Dewey ID to appropriate category table above
# Format: | φ.X.X.X | Name | path/to/file | φ |

# When: Pattern detected between files
# What: Update nexus-graph (φ.5.1.0)
echo "φ.X.X.X → π.Y.Y.Y, e.Z.Z.Z" >> Nexus-MC/Nexus_graph_v2.skill

# Capacity: Read-only for structure, append-only for logs
```

### π-tier: MONAD-MEMORY
```bash
# When: Regenerating context from seeds
# What: Log regeneration events
echo "$(date -Iseconds)|REGEN|source:φ.X.X.X|target:π.Y.Y.Y" >> .claude/brain/regen_log

# When: Connection patterns discovered
# What: Update connection layer
# Store in: Nexus-MC/connections/

# Capacity: Can update connection files, regenerate structures
```

### e-tier: NEXUS-CORE
```bash
# When: Working with base concepts actively
# What: Update concept files, track modifications
echo "$(date -Iseconds)|UPDATE|e.8.0.3/concepts/X|reason" >> .claude/brain/nexus_core_log

# When: New concept emerges
# What: Create new concept file in Nexus-MC/nexus-core/concepts/
# Format: concept-name.md with proper metadata

# Capacity: Can create/update concept files, entities, references
```

### i-tier: NEXUS-MIND
```bash
# When: Deep synthesis work, mastery-level insights
# What: Append to deep memory files
echo "$(date -Iseconds)|SYNTHESIS|topic|insight" >> .claude/brain/nexus_mind_log

# When: Major breakthrough or pattern integration
# What: Update nexus-mind files with new connections
# Location: Nexus-MC/nexus-mind/

# Capacity: Append-only for most files, careful updates to preserve deep memory
```

### φ.5.1.0: NEXUS-GRAPH
```bash
# When: Two+ Dewey IDs accessed together 3+ times
# What: Create link in nexus-graph
echo "LINK: φ.A.A.A → π.B.B.B (co-accessed: 3x, pattern: topic_name)" >> Nexus-MC/Nexus_graph_v2.skill

# When: Pattern becomes clear (5+ occurrences)
# What: Define named pattern
cat >> Nexus-MC/Nexus_graph_v2.skill <<EOF
PATTERN: pattern_name
  φ.A.A.A (Description)
  π.B.B.B (Description)
  e.C.C.C (Description)
EOF

# When: Multiple patterns relate
# What: Create meta-pattern
# Format: META-PATTERN: name \n  PATTERN: x \n  PATTERN: y

# Capacity: Append-only for new links/patterns, can refactor when proven stable
```

### Git-Brain Analytics
```bash
# When: Any file accessed
record_access() {
    local dewey_id="$1"
    local context="$2"
    echo "$(date -Iseconds)|${dewey_id}|${context}" >> .claude/brain/access_log
}

# When: Novel co-access pattern (never seen before)
record_novel_pattern() {
    local pattern_desc="$1"
    local dewey_ids="$2"  # comma-separated
    echo "$(date -Iseconds)|NOVEL|${pattern_desc}|${dewey_ids}" >> .claude/brain/novel_patterns
}

# When: Error encountered and resolved
record_error_solution() {
    local error_hash=$(echo "$error" | git hash-object --stdin)
    local solution="$1"
    echo "${error_hash}|${solution}|$(date -Iseconds)" >> .claude/brain/error_patterns
}

# Daily maintenance (run at session end)
daily_maintenance() {
    # Archive old logs if >1000 entries
    [ $(wc -l < .claude/brain/access_log) -gt 1000 ] && archive_logs
    
    # Consolidate patterns (5+ occurrences → known)
    consolidate_patterns
    
    # Update nexus-graph from co-access patterns
    detect_and_update_nexus_graph
}
```

### Session Logging
```bash
# When: Start of session with MONAD work
log_session_start() {
    local session_id="$(date -Iseconds)"
    echo "SESSION_START|${session_id}|$(git log -1 --format=%h)" >> .claude/brain/session_log
}

# When: End of session
log_session_end() {
    echo "SESSION_END|$(date -Iseconds)|files_accessed:$(grep "$(date -I)" .claude/brain/access_log | wc -l)" >> .claude/brain/session_log
    daily_maintenance
}

# When: New pattern emerges during session
log_session_insight() {
    local insight="$1"
    local related_ids="$2"
    echo "$(date -Iseconds)|INSIGHT|${insight}|${related_ids}" >> claudes_log/$(date -I)_session_insights.md
}
```

### Capacity Guidelines

**φ-tier (GREMLIN-BRAIN-V2)**:
- ✓ CAN: Update Dewey index tables (add new IDs)
- ✓ CAN: Append to access logs
- ✓ CAN: Update nexus-graph links
- ✗ CANNOT: Delete entries (preserve history)
- ✗ CANNOT: Restructure categories (0-9 are fixed)

**π-tier (MONAD-MEMORY)**:
- ✓ CAN: Update connection files
- ✓ CAN: Regenerate structures from φ-tier seeds
- ✓ CAN: Create new regeneration patterns
- ✗ CANNOT: Modify core generators (those are in φ-tier)

**e-tier (NEXUS-CORE)**:
- ✓ CAN: Create/update concept files
- ✓ CAN: Add entities as they emerge
- ✓ CAN: Expand references
- ✗ CANNOT: Delete established concepts without reason
- ⚠ CAREFUL: Updates should extend, not replace

**i-tier (NEXUS-MIND)**:
- ✓ CAN: Append to deep memory files
- ✓ CAN: Add synthesis insights
- ⚠ CAREFUL: Rarely update (only for corrections or major breakthroughs)
- ✗ AVOID: Frequent changes (deep memory should be stable)

**Nexus-Graph (φ.5.1.0)**:
- ✓ CAN: Add new links (φ.X → π.Y → e.Z)
- ✓ CAN: Define patterns from repeated co-access
- ✓ CAN: Create meta-patterns
- ✓ CAN: Update pattern descriptions
- ✗ CANNOT: Remove links without documenting why

